Hello,

Join us for alive, interactive online coursedesigned to strengthen your 
understanding of statistical modelling using R. The course is divided 
intofive modules(approximately40 hoursin total), each combininglive 
teaching sessionswithhands-on exercises using real datasets. All 
sessions are also available ason-demand videos, and adedicated 
discussion boardensures daily interaction between instructors and 
participants.

You?ll also receive aone-hour personal video meetingwith the instructors 
for tailored feedback and guidance.

*Course content*
We begin with a concise introduction to R and a step-by-step protocol 
for data exploration to help you avoid common statistical pitfalls. 
You?ll learn how to detect outliers, address collinearity, and apply 
transformations. We then move on tomultiple linear regression, explained 
from a biological perspective, and discuss common issues and how to 
solve them.

Next, we introducegeneralised linear models (GLMs)for analysing count, 
continuous, presence?absence, and proportional data. Finally, we 
exploregeneralised additive models (GAMs)? a flexible smoothing 
technique for situations where parametric models such as linear 
regression or GLMs are not sufficient.

Whether you?re new to R or looking to deepen your applied statistical 
skills, this course will give you the tools and confidence to analyse 
real-world data effectively.


